USB mode screen-recording demo (reproducible).

Prerequisites: git, bash, built ./git-fire at repo root (make build).
Optional recording: X11 display, xfce4-terminal, ffmpeg.

  bash demo/usb_mode/usb_mode_demo_run.sh
    Uses isolated HOME under /tmp; creates a "virtual USB" folder and runs
    git-fire with --usb / config [[usb.targets]].

  bash demo/usb_mode/record_demo.sh
    Records wrap_demo.sh in a terminal window; writes MP4 + GIFs next to this file.
